@startuml
title Form Submission to Case Update — Sequence Diagram

actor "Patient/Clinician" as User
participant "UI\n(PatientQuestionnaireForm / Case forms)" as UI
participant "client/forms" as Client
participant "service/forms" as Forms
participant "service/journeyResolver" as Resolver
participant "service/policy" as Policy
participant "service/cases" as Cases
participant "service/audit" as Audit
participant "patchStore" as Store

User -> UI : Submit questionnaire answers
UI -> Client : submitFormResponse(patientId, caseId, templateId, answers, journeyContext?)
Client -> Forms : submitFormResponse(...)
Forms -> Forms : Validate template/questions
Forms -> Forms : Compute scores from scoringRules
Forms -> Store : Save FormResponse
Store --> Forms : persisted FormResponse

Forms -> Cases : touch case lastActivityAt
Cases -> Store : patch case fields/triggers when needed
Store --> Cases : updated case

Forms -> Resolver : buildPolicyScopeWithAliases(caseId)
Resolver --> Forms : numeric scope
Forms -> Policy : evaluatePolicyRules(caseId, scope)
Policy -> Store : update Case.policyWarnings
Store --> Policy : updated case warnings

Forms -> Audit : addAuditEvent(FORM_SUBMITTED, context)
Audit -> Store : append audit event
Store --> Audit : persisted event

Forms --> Client : FormResponse + updated case context
Client --> UI : success
UI -> UI : Show success snack\nrefetch due steps / case view

note right of Forms
  Journey context may include:
  patientJourneyId, journeyTemplateEntryId,
  occurrenceIndex
end note

@enduml